We’ve always been a very public non traditional relationship and with our new found life and home in LA it felt right to officially start a real family. I will catch a lot of shit for not pulling out but I’m old and I am ready to pass the torch to our future little whisperer.

Throwback Thursday showcasing all my injuries since meeting @slutwhisperer. 🤦🏽‍♀️
I’m a genius!

On Friday afternoon, I received the worst call of my life that no one can prepare you for. I am in denial right now typing this because you don’t think it’s ever gonna happen to you until it does.  I can’t process that you’re no longer with us. 

When I was just about your age, I cradled your little body in my arms and I became a first time Aunt to one of the most beautiful souls. I didn’t even know how to hold a baby. My brother was still a kid himself at your age (20) and yet we all were there figuring it all out together as a family. I was so proud to see you grow up to be a true gentleman, kind, selfless, hard working, intelligent man with the most contagious smile. We were just talking about celebrating your first legal drink together in Vegas when you hit 21 in October. 

I’m lost, confused, heartbroken, angry, helpless and all I want to do is hug you one more time but all I can do is just cry into my pillow and hope this is an awful nightmare and I can wake up now. 

Life isn’t fair but in the short time that you had, you were very loved by so many people and it was an easy kind of love. I consider myself and anyone who got to even spend one day with you lucky because that’s how much of an impact you made and that gives me a little bit of peace through all this tragedy.  I’ll see you one day again for that long hug and take that much needed shot with you. 

I love you Elijah. 💔

From the moment I met you, something in me changed. I was challenged; I became more sensitive, confident, and more secure than I had ever been in my life, all because of you. You always bring out the best in the people around you, and your energy is contagious. People naturally gravitate towards you, and you’re genuinely loved by so many people. You’re simply a really cool guy, and you’re my guy. I adore you so much, and I’m incredibly grateful to have you in my life every day. You showed me what true selflessness looks like when we went through the hardest thing in our lives recently. There you were, standing by me and stepping up when I needed you the most. You were my rock without hesitation. I am truly fortunate to have you, and as you say, “I’m the catch in this relationship.” It’s true, you are, bub.

But I must say, I get excited this time of year because we can be the same age for exactly 60 days, and I like to make that known. Happy 39th birthday @slutwhisperer! I love you! ❤️🎂

2023 has been a bitch and taken one of the most important beautiful souls in our lives from our family. Elijah, you are 21 today and we should be hitting up bars and I would love to be holding your hair back from taking too many shots. Instead, I’m writing everything I would say to you here. I love and adore you so much, life isn’t the same without you here. 

We're all doing our best, holding your memory close, and striving to live our lives as you would have wanted. My heart is shattered, and life's just not fair. You had so much to see and experience, and I'll do my best to live it out in your honor. I'll keep your memory alive for as long as I'm here and until the day I get to see your beautiful face again with one big bear hug. Happy Birthday my angel. 💜
